Ryanair May Send Passengers Text Messages About Delays, FTD Says

-- B y   N a o m i   K r e s g e
-- 
2011-05-18T02:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-18/ryanair-may-send-passengers-text-messages-about-delays-ftd-says.html
Ryanair Holdings Plc (RYA)  may begin
notifying passengers via text message about delays or changes to
their flights,  Financial Times Deutschland  reported, citing an
interview with Chief Executive Officer  Michael O’Leary .  The carrier plans to spend less than 10 million euros
($14.2 million) on a passenger communication system to go into
 service  in summer 2012, the newspaper quoted O’Leary as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Naomi Kresge in Berlin at 
 nkresge@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Phil Serafino at   pserafino@bloomberg.net  